"Food processing plant" includes:
A bakery plant;
A cannery;
A confectionery plant;
A crab meat picking plant;
A food manufacturing plant;
A food warehouse or distribution center;
A frozen food processing plant;
An ice manufacturing plant;
A shellfish plant;
A soft drink manufacturing plant; or
A bottled water plant.

"Food service facility" does not include:
A kitchen in a private home where food is prepared at no charge for guests in the home, for guests at a social gathering, or for service to unemployed, homeless, or other disadvantaged populations;
A food preparation or serving area where only nonpotentially hazardous food, as defined by the United States Food and Drug Administration, is prepared or served only by an excluded organization;
A location in a farmer's market or at a public festival or event where raw agricultural products, as defined in § 21-304(d)(1)(iii) of this subtitle, are sold; or
A cottage food business.

"Semipermanent food service facility" means a food service facility that:
Is built at a location other than where it operates;
Is transported as a complete unit that does not require a building permit to install on the location at which it operates;
Has no indoor seating for patrons; and
When serving cooked food, serves only foods cooked for immediate service.

"Semipermanent food service facility" does not include a food service facility that is a mechanically, electrically, manually, or otherwise propelled vehicle operating on land or water that moves as part of its routine operation to:
Change location for sales;
Obtain food and other supplies;
Fill potable water supply holding tanks;
Empty wastewater holding tanks; or
Provide for the cleaning and sanitation of equipment and utensils.
